<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4676655>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 1. Crania of Gallinula tenebrosa AM O.67057 (A,C,F) and Australlus disneyi QM F23806 (B,D,E,G) in right lateral (A,B,F), ventral (C,D), caudal (E), and dorsolateral (G) views. Abbreviations: cnt, crista nuchalis transversus; fo, fonticuli orbitocranialis; fol, facet os lacrimale; fm, foramen magnum; ft, fossa temporalis; nh, nasofrontal hinge; pp, processus paroccipitalis; rt, recessus tympanicus. Scale bar for (A–E) is 20 mm and (F, G) is 5 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4676655/files/figure.png" .

